Jon C Russo (jrusso@atl.ge.com) writes:

> Does anyone out there have a good CRC algorithm or the like, that boarders on
> a signature generator? 

What do you mean by "a signature generator"? CRCs are good for
detecting random errors, but I am getting the impression that this is
not what you want.

> I want to make sure that it is incredibly difficult
> to modify a text file.

It is incredibly easy to modify a text file - just use a text editor.
:-) Do you mean that it must be incredibly difficult to modify the
text file WITHOUT MODIFYING ITS CHECKSUM? If this is the case, then
you need a cryptographically strong hash function. A few good ones are
MD4, MD5, SHS,... You can find descriptions and implementations of
them on our ftp site:

ftp.informatik.uni-hamburg.de:/pub/virus/texts/crypto/

files md4.zip, md5.zip, shs.zip.

Regards,
Vesselin
